ww.cbr.com/marvel-shang-chi-largely-asian-cast/ |archive-date=December 31, 2019 |access-date=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Yeoh\">{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/marvel/2020/01/21/shang-chi-michelle-yeoh-cast-role-marvel/ |title=Michelle Yeoh In Talks For Marvel's Shang-Chi |last=Davis |first=Brandon |date=January 21, 2020 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200121203748/https://comicbook.com/marvel/2020/01/21/shang-chi-michelle-yeoh-cast-role-marvel/ |archive-date=January 21, 2020 |access-date=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NorringtonLee\">{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/marvel-movie-tv-projects-abandoned/|title=15 Abandoned Marvel Movie/TV Projects That We Never Got To See|last=Craig|first=Andrew|date=March 30, 2018 |website=[[ScreenRant]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307151037/https://screenrant.com/marvel-movie-tv-projects-abandoned/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> \n\n<ref name=\"BloodyDisgusting\">{{Cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/editorials/3601107/breaking-deleted-blade-ending-featuring-morbius-never-saw/|title=Breaking Down the Deleted 'Blade' Ending Featuring Morbius and Why We Never Got That Sequel|last=Brehmer|first=Nat|date=January 16, 2020 |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307151925/https://bloody-disgusting.com/editorials/3601107/breaking-deleted-blade-ending-featuring-morbius-never-saw/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> \n\n<ref name=\"Dreamworks\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.awn.com/news/marvel-puts-shang-chi-dreamworks-hands|title=Marvel Puts Shang Chi In DreamWorks' Hands |last=Balsley|first=Sarah|date=April 15, 2003 |website=[[Animation World Network]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307155609/https://www.awn.com/news/marvel-puts-shang-chi-dreamworks-hands |archive-date=March 